programme.title: Election 2016
programme.desc: Huw Edwards presents full through-the-night coverage as the first results of the UK-wide elections come in, revealing the winners in the battle for the Scottish Parliament and Welsh Assembly. There will also be results from many of the local councils in England as well as the outcome of elections for police commissioners and city mayors. Jeremy Vine and Emily Maitlis analyse the results as they come in, while Laura Kuenssberg assesses the impact they will have in the days, week and years ahead.(n)
